They tried it in the 1930s, when there was a surge in technology thanks to America and the Allies, they were pushed back down—even in America, there was an attempted coup by a rather rich family we all know. 
They failed only when they were threatened with treason.

2001 was another coup—and this time, they won.
Now they’re using technology to control what we see, what we think, and how we behave.
The world of our parents and grandparents is gone forever.
This is the future, and it’s all about control.
